OL,3,CHigh temperatures could mean hottest
OL,4,Cbank holiday on record
OL,6,FTom Morgan, a Met Office
OL,7,Fmeteorologist, told the Press
OL,8,FAssociation: "We rarely see
OL,9,Ftemperatures above 35C, even in the
OL,10,Fsummer months, so to see temperatures
OL,11,Fgetting close to 35C in May is, as I
OL,12,Fsay, pretty historic."
OL,14,FWales and Northern Ireland also
OL,15,Freached 2026 record temperatures of
OL,16,F27.4C in Cardiff and 23.4C in Armagh
OL,17,Fon Sunday.
OL,26,@pD@NOUtD@VO]
