OL,3,CHigh temperatures could mean hottest
OL,4,Cbank holiday on record
OL,6,FAge UK recommends staying inside
OL,7,Fduring the hottest hours of the day,
OL,8,Fbetween 11am and 3pm, and having
OL,9,Fregular cold baths or showers.
OL,11,FAge UK charity director Caroline
OL,12,FAbrahams said: "We can all help older
OL,13,Fpeople stay safe during periods of hot
OL,14,Fweather by checking in on older
OL,15,Frelatives, friends and neighbours to
OL,16,Fsee if they need anything or are
OL,17,Fstruggling with the heat.
OL,19,F"Offering to pick up shopping or
OL,20,Fmedication, or even lending a fan, can
OL,21,Fmake a real difference."
